        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 5:49PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 549 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Bound Brook, or near Somerville, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Elizabeth, Bayonne, Plainfield, Linden, Todt Hill, The Verrazano
Narrows Bridge, Port Richmond, Clark, Tompkinsville, Oakwood, Rahway,
Scotch Plains, Cranford, New Dorp, and Roselle.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
